@novnc/novnc 1.7.0

Vendored 2026-07-17 via `npm pack @novnc/novnc@1.7.0` (registry tarball
sha512-ucEJOx4T2avIR[...]ElNFouK13RzyA==, shasum 7f832cf07c66475a81a25708b8e5299a5c4efec5).

Contents copied verbatim from the npm package (no build step run — this is
already the published, browser-usable ES module source):
  - core/            noVNC's RFB client and all its runtime dependencies
                      (crypto, decoders, input, display, websock, etc.)
  - vendor/pako/      zlib inflate/deflate, imported by core/inflator.js and
                      core/deflator.js (needed by the tight/zrle decoders)
  - LICENSE.txt, AUTHORS

Not vendored (not needed to load `RFB` as an ES module in a browser):
  - docs/, README.md, package.json, app/ (noVNC's own demo UI), tests,
    build tooling, po/ translations.

Entry point: core/rfb.js, default-exports the `RFB` class
(package.json "exports": "./core/rfb.js").

To re-vendor a newer version: `npm pack @novnc/novnc@<version>`, extract,
replace core/ and vendor/pako/ wholesale, update this file.
